10/06/2004
SISAK, Croatia -- The Mine Action Centre said Wednesday (9 June) its results in the first months of this year exceeded projections.
The centre said it had implemented 84 mine clearing projects and searched 17.6 square km of land for mines.
It found and cleared 1,076 land mines and 149 pieces of live ordnance left over from the conflicts of the 1990s.
The report said six people were killed by exploding mines, including two disposal experts.
(HINA - 09/06/04)
